---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Daily Routine">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>Daily Routine</h1>
      <p>My structured daily plan for recovery and building a stronger body.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="routine">
      <section class="time-block card">
        <div class="time-badge">Morning</div>
        <h2>Wake Up & Prep</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Wake up with 8 hours sleep</label></li>
          <li>
            <label><input type="checkbox" /> 5 min stretching in bed</label>
            <details class="item-detail">
              <summary>What to do</summary>
              <div class="item-detail-content">
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>Stretch</th><th>Duration</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Full body stretch (arms overhead, toes pointed)</td><td>30 sec</td><td>Reach as far as you can</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Knees to chest</td><td>30 sec</td><td>Hug both knees, gentle rock side to side</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Supine spinal twist (each side)</td><td>30 sec × 2</td><td>Keep shoulders flat on bed</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Hamstring stretch (each leg)</td><td>30 sec × 2</td><td>Use towel or hands behind thigh</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Hip flexor stretch (each side)</td><td>30 sec × 2</td><td>Bring knee to chest, extend other leg</td></tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
                <p class="detail-note">Equipment: None — bed only. Keep it gentle. The goal is to wake up the body, not push hard.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Drink cold water (300–500 mL)</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Splash cold water on face</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Breakfast</label></li>
        </ul>
        <details class="why-section">
          <summary>Why I do this</summary>
          <div class="why-content">
            <p>Sleep is the main way body fixes itself. So, ensure 8 hours of sleep.
            With the body in a bad shape, stretching in bed helps with starting the day off with movements with no excuse and it hurts way less compared to stretching on the ground.</p>
            <p>During deep sleep, the body releases human growth hormone (HGH) for tissue repair and muscle recovery. Even a single night of poor sleep reduces insulin sensitivity by 19–25%. Sleep is Step Zero — without it, nothing else works.</p>
            <p>Morning stretching lowers blood glucose by up to 28 mg/dL per session and reduces blood pressure — sometimes more effectively than walking. It also activates the parasympathetic nervous system, shifting the body from stress mode to recovery mode.</p>
            <p>Cold water first thing addresses overnight dehydration (improving alertness and mood immediately), activates the vagus nerve via the mammalian diving reflex (shifting the nervous system toward recovery), and provides a small metabolic boost. Splashing cold water on the face amplifies the vagal activation significantly more than drinking alone.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <section class="time-block card">
        <div class="time-badge">Mid-Morning</div>
        <h2>Movement & Exercise</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>
            <label><input type="checkbox" /> Warm up (5 min)</label>
            <details class="item-detail">
              <summary>What to do</summary>
              <div class="item-detail-content">
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Duration / Reps</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>
                    <tr><td>March in place</td><td>1 min</td><td>Lift knees to comfortable height</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Arm circles</td><td>30 sec forward, 30 sec back</td><td>Small to large circles</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Leg swings (each leg)</td><td>30 sec × 2</td><td>Hold wall for balance</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Gentle torso twists</td><td>1 min</td><td>Arms relaxed, rotate side to side</td></tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
                <p class="detail-note">Equipment: None. Goal is to get blood flowing and joints moving before exercise.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
          <li>
            <label><input type="checkbox" /> Exercise routine (30–45 min)</label>
            <details class="item-detail">
              <summary>What to do</summary>
              <div class="item-detail-content">
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th><th>Equipment</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Walk (brisk)</td><td>20–30 min</td><td>None</td><td>Outdoors if possible for sunlight</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Bodyweight squats (or to chair)</td><td>3 × 10</td><td>Chair for support</td><td>Go as low as comfortable</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Wall push-ups</td><td>3 × 10</td><td>Wall</td><td>Progress to incline/floor over time</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Standing calf raises</td><td>3 × 15</td><td>Wall for balance</td><td>Slow up, slow down</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Dead hang or arm raise</td><td>3 × 15–30 sec</td><td>Bar or doorframe</td><td>If no bar, raise arms overhead</td></tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
                <p class="detail-note">Adjust reps and sets to your current level. The goal is consistency, not intensity. Progress gradually week by week.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
          <li>
            <label><input type="checkbox" /> Cool down & stretch (10 min)</label>
            <details class="item-detail">
              <summary>What to do</summary>
              <div class="item-detail-content">
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>Stretch</th><th>Duration</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Standing quad stretch (each leg)</td><td>30 sec × 2</td><td>Hold wall for balance</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Standing hamstring stretch (each leg)</td><td>30 sec × 2</td><td>Foot on low step or curb</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Calf stretch against wall (each leg)</td><td>30 sec × 2</td><td>Keep heel on ground</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Chest opener (doorway stretch)</td><td>30 sec</td><td>Arms on doorframe, lean through</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Neck rolls</td><td>30 sec each direction</td><td>Slow and gentle</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Child's pose or forward fold</td><td>1 min</td><td>Relax and breathe deeply</td></tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
                <p class="detail-note">Equipment: None. Hold each stretch gently — no bouncing. Breathe slowly through each one.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Post-workout nutrition</label></li>
        </ul>
        <details class="why-section">
          <summary>Why I do this</summary>
          <div class="why-content">
            <p>A body that stops moving starts dying. A fit older person can lose 25% of their strength in just 2 weeks of inactivity. After a decade of not moving, reversing this is the most important thing I can do.</p>
            <p>Walking increases muscle glucose uptake up to fivefold through insulin-independent mechanisms. A 10-minute walk after eating significantly reduces blood sugar spikes. The glucose-lowering effect of exercise continues for up to 48 hours — which is why never skipping more than 1 day matters.</p>
            <p>Even 10 minutes of daily walking reduces mortality risk. The long-term goal is 60–75 minutes of moderate activity daily — the threshold that eliminates the excess mortality risk from sedentary behavior. Getting sunlight during the walk also sets the circadian clock for better sleep.</p>
            <p>The cool-down stretch after exercise isn't just for flexibility — stretching reduces post-exercise blood pressure by ~10 mmHg, improves arterial health, and stimulates nitric oxide release which dilates blood vessels and reduces inflammation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <section class="time-block card">
        <div class="time-badge">Afternoon</div>
        <h2>Recovery & Nutrition</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Healthy lunch</label></li>
          <li>
            <label><input type="checkbox" /> Walk / light movement (15–20 min)</label>
            <details class="item-detail">
              <summary>What to do</summary>
              <div class="item-detail-content">
                <p>Post-lunch walk at a comfortable pace. Aim for 15–20 minutes. This is specifically for glucose management — walking after meals reduces blood sugar spikes significantly.</p>
                <p class="detail-note">Equipment: None. Outdoors preferred. Even pacing around the house counts.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
          <li>
            <label><input type="checkbox" /> Foam rolling or massage</label>
            <details class="item-detail">
              <summary>What to do</summary>
              <div class="item-detail-content">
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Duration</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Calves</td><td>1 min each</td><td>Roll slowly, pause on tender spots</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Quads / IT band</td><td>1 min each side</td><td>Use body weight to control pressure</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Upper back</td><td>2 min</td><td>Arms crossed over chest</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Glutes</td><td>1 min each side</td><td>Sit on roller, cross ankle over knee</td></tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
                <p class="detail-note">Equipment: Foam roller (or tennis ball for targeted spots). Skip areas that feel too painful — work up to them.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Hydration check</label></li>
        </ul>
        <details class="why-section">
          <summary>Why I do this</summary>
          <div class="why-content">
            <p>A post-lunch walk is one of the single best things for glucose control. Walking after meals reduces postprandial blood sugar spikes significantly. Even breaking up prolonged sitting with 3–5 minutes of light walking every 20–30 minutes improves glycemic control.</p>
            <p>Each hour of daily sitting is associated with a 2% increase in all-cause mortality risk. People who sit more than 10 hours/day and are inactive have the highest mortality risk of any group studied. The afternoon walk directly counters this.</p>
            <p>Foam rolling and self-massage support recovery by improving blood flow to tissues and reducing muscle tension. Staying well-hydrated throughout the day lowers cortisol reactivity to stress — meaning a well-hydrated body handles stress better than a dehydrated one.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <section class="time-block card">
        <div class="time-badge">Evening</div>
        <h2>Wind Down</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Healthy dinner</label></li>
          <li>
            <label><input type="checkbox" /> Evening stretch / yoga (10–15 min)</label>
            <details class="item-detail">
              <summary>What to do</summary>
              <div class="item-detail-content">
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>Stretch</th><th>Duration</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Cat-cow (on hands and knees)</td><td>1 min</td><td>Sync with breathing</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Seated forward fold</td><td>1 min</td><td>Reach for toes, bend knees if needed</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Pigeon pose (each side)</td><td>1 min × 2</td><td>Use pillow under hip if needed</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Supine figure-4 stretch (each side)</td><td>1 min × 2</td><td>Great for hip tightness</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Legs up the wall</td><td>3–5 min</td><td>Activates parasympathetic system</td></tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
                <p class="detail-note">Equipment: Yoga mat or carpet. Pillow optional. Focus on deep, slow breathing — this is as much for the nervous system as for flexibility.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Journal / diary entry</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Prepare for tomorrow</label></li>
        </ul>
        <details class="why-section">
          <summary>Why I do this</summary>
          <div class="why-content">
            <p>Evening stretching activates the parasympathetic nervous system — the "rest and digest" mode. Studies show that stretching significantly decreases salivary cortisol and enhances parasympathetic nerve activity as measured by heart rate variability. This directly prepares the body for quality sleep.</p>
            <p>Stretching in supine and inverted positions (like legs up the wall) stimulates baroreceptor activity, which reflexively lowers blood pressure, reduces stress hormones, and calms brain activity. This is as much for the nervous system as for flexibility.</p>
            <p>12 weeks of regular stretching improves vascular function, reduces arterial stiffness, and induces positive arterial remodelling — benefits that persist even after stopping. The evening session compounds with the morning stretches for cumulative vascular and metabolic benefit.</p>
            <p>Journaling and preparing for tomorrow creates accountability and reduces the mental load that can interfere with falling asleep.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <section class="time-block card">
        <div class="time-badge">Night</div>
        <h2>Sleep</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> No screens 30 min before bed</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" /> Lights out at least 4 hours after a meal</label></li>
        </ul>
        <details class="why-section">
          <summary>Why I do this</summary>
          <div class="why-content">
            <p>Sleep is Step Zero. During deep sleep, the body releases human growth hormone for tissue repair, the brain's glymphatic system clears metabolic waste, and the immune system produces cytokines for infection defense and tissue healing. Without sleep, none of this happens.</p>
            <p>Sleep deprivation directly causes insulin resistance — even one night of poor sleep reduces insulin sensitivity by 19–25%. One week of sleeping ~5 hours/night significantly reduces insulin sensitivity in healthy people. The good news: three nights of catch-up sleep can reduce insulin resistance by ~20%.</p>
            <p>Screens before bed suppress melatonin production. A wind-down routine with dim lights signals the body to prepare for sleep. The American Heart Association now recognizes sleep as one of their "Life's Essential 8" for cardiovascular health.</p>
            <p>Eating at least 4 hours before sleep ensures the body isn't still digesting, which can fragment sleep architecture and raise overnight blood glucose.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <div class="reset-bar">
        <button id="reset-btn" class="btn-reset">Reset All Checkboxes</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const STORAGE_KEY = 'fbb-routine-checks';

  function loadState() {
    try {
      const saved = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);
      if (!saved) return;
      const state = JSON.parse(saved);
      const boxes = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLInputElement>('.checklist input[type="checkbox"]');
      boxes.forEach((box, i) => {
        if (state[i]) box.checked = true;
      });
    } catch {}
  }

  function saveState() {
    const boxes = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLInputElement>('.checklist input[type="checkbox"]');
    const state = Array.from(boxes).map((b) => b.checked);
    localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, JSON.stringify(state));
  }

  loadState();

  document.querySelectorAll('.checklist input[type="checkbox"]').forEach((box) => {
    box.addEventListener('change', saveState);
  });

  document.getElementById('reset-btn')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    document.querySelectorAll<HTMLInputElement>('.checklist input[type="checkbox"]').forEach((box) => {
      box.checked = false;
    });
    localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEY);
  });
</script>

<style>
  .routine {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .time-block {
    position: relative;
    padding-top: 2.25rem;
  }

  .time-badge {
    position: absolute;
    top: -0.75rem;
    left: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .time-block h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .checklist {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .checklist li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .checklist li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .checklist label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .checklist input[type='checkbox'] {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    accent-color: var(--color-primary);
    cursor: pointer;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .checklist input[type='checkbox']:checked + span,
  .checklist label:has(input:checked) {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-decoration: line-through;
  }

  /* Item detail expandable sections */
  .item-detail {
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.25rem 2.75rem;
  }

  .item-detail summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 0.825rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    padding: 0.15rem 0;
    user-select: none;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .item-detail summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .item-detail summary::before {
    content: '▸';
    display: inline-block;
    transition: transform 0.2s;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
  }

  .item-detail[open] summary::before {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
  }

  .item-detail summary:hover {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .item-detail-content {
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .item-detail-content table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .item-detail-content th {
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding: 0.4rem 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .item-detail-content td {
    padding: 0.35rem 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-bg-alt);
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .item-detail-content tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .detail-note {
    font-size: 0.825rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .item-detail-content p {
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
  }

  /* Why section */
  .why-section {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .why-section summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 0.25rem 0;
    user-select: none;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .why-section summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .why-section summary::before {
    content: '▸';
    display: inline-block;
    transition: transform 0.2s;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .why-section[open] summary::before {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
  }

  .why-section summary:hover {
    color: var(--color-primary-dark);
  }

  .why-content {
    padding: 0.75rem 0 0.25rem 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.925rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
  }

  .why-content p {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .why-content p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .reset-bar {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1rem 0;
  }

  .btn-reset {
    background: none;
    border: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    padding: 0.5rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .btn-reset:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .item-detail {
      margin-left: 2rem;
    }

    .item-detail-content table {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
    }

    .item-detail-content th,
    .item-detail-content td {
      padding: 0.3rem 0.35rem;
    }
  }
</style>
